Package edu.uiuc.ncsa.qdl.expressions

Expressions are objects that take zero or more arguments and return a result.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ExpressionNode
    This class mostly manages the structure of expressions (so arguments are the children) and evaluating them is delegating the result to the OpEvaluator class.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Assignment
    Once evaluated, this will return its value as the result.
    AssignmentNode
    In order to use chained assignments (a := b += c -= d ...) we need to wrap an assignment in an ExpressionNode so it can get daisy chained.

Package edu.uiuc.ncsa.qdl.expressions Description

Expressions are objects that take zero or more arguments and return a result. These are the classes that model this. he are processed by AbstractFunctionEvaluator and its subclasses.

Created by Jeff Gaynor
on 3/13/20 at 9:01 AM
